result.execSummary:
The defendant Isaiah Matthew Washington was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Provide a specimen for DNA testing. Pay mandatory costs, assessment and surcharges or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant.

Court advised the defendant he cannot possess firearms, must provide a DNA specimen and surcharge for testing and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.

If defendant possess a firearm within 5 years of completing this sentence, he will be subject to a mandatory 3 year initial confinement.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
- No violations of the criminal law rising to the level of probable cause.
- Do not use or possess any illegally controlled substances.
- Random screening.
- AODA, treatment or programs.
- Obtain GED.
- No Contact with any store at the Mayfair Mall or Target Stores.
